article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 50, Nicholls St. 47
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Chris Daniels hit a 3-pointer to lift Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 50-47 win over Nicholls State Thursday. Daniels made the 3-pointer with 29 seconds left and Nicholls was forced to foul after Ryan Bathie missed a jumper with eight seconds left. Daniels led the Islanders (7-15, 4-5 Southland Conference) with 19 points, hitting 4-of-7 shots from the floor and grabbing nine rebounds. Anatoly Bose and Adonis Gray each scored 10 points to lead Nicholls (7-18, 2-8). The Islanders dominated the glass, outrebounding Nicholls 47-27.
